{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_56","type":"agent_message","text":"The `MemorySegment` indirection is turning into noise unrelated to the actual reachability defect. I’m simplifying those codec tests back to ordinary byte-array round trips so they still trigger `create()` and the native loader paths, but don’t require preview or JDK reflection metadata that the library itself doesn’t own."}}
2026-05-18T21:57:45.378568Z ERROR codex_core::tools::router: error=apply_patch verification failed: Failed to find expected lines in /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/7017-f7e75512/tests/src/io.airlift/aircompressor/2.0/src/test/java/io_airlift/aircompressor/LzoUnsafeUtilTest.java:
    @Test
    void compressesAndDecompressesDirectBuffers() {
        byte[] input = repeatedPayload();
        LzoCompressor compressor = new LzoCompressor();
        LzoDecompressor decompressor = new LzoDecompressor();

        ByteBuffer source = ByteBuffer.allocateDirect(input.length);
        source.put(input);
        source.flip();

        ByteBuffer compressed = ByteBuffer.allocateDirect(compressor.maxCompressedLength(input.length));
        int compressedLength = ForeignMemorySegmentSupport.invokeCodec(LzoCompressor.class, compressor, "compress", source, compressed);
        assertThat(compressedLength).isPositive();

        compressed.limit(compressedLength);
        compressed.position(0);
        ByteBuffer restored = ByteBuffer.allocateDirect(input.length);
        int restoredLength = decompressor.decompress(MemorySegment.ofBuffer(compressed), MemorySegment.ofBuffer(restored));

        restored.limit(restoredLength);
        restored.position(0);
        byte[] actual = new byte[restoredLength];
        restored.get(actual);
        assertThat(actual).isEqualTo(input);
    }
